7.6.3 Mode and Global Phonetic Parameters

Antoin Rodgers

knitr::opts_chunk$set(warning = F, message = F, tidy = "styler")

# Load Functions.
source("../../2_R_Functions/myFunctions.R") 

# Load packages.
installMissingPackages(
  c(
    # Include statistical packages.
    "performance",
    "lmerTest",
    "lme4",
    "optimx",
    "MuMIn",
    # Include packages for tidy output.
    "tidyverse",
    "stringr",
    "broomExtra",
    "janitor",
    "sjPlot",
    "formattable",
    "knitr",
    "RColorBrewer",
    # Include packages for %in% %notin% syntactic notation
    "mefa4"
  )
)

# Load Corpus
m_corpus <- get_m_corpus("../../4_data/m_corpus.csv")  %>%
  select(speaker,
         gender,
         mode,
         utt_mean_f0,
         utt_slope,
         phr_phon,
         acc_phon,
         fin_phon,
         prompt) %>%
  mutate(h_start = if_else(!is.na((str_extract(phr_phon, "%H|\\^\\[%H|% H\\*"))),
                           "H start",
                           "no H start"),
         h_start = factor(h_start, levels = c("H start", "no H start")),
         fin_phon = factor(str_replace_all(fin_phon, "\\^|\\[|\\]", ""),
                           levels = c("%", "L%"))
         )

1. Mode-and-Phonoogy Models

Utterance mean f0

utt_mean_f0_full_mdl <- lmer(
  utt_mean_f0 ~ mode + gender
    + (1 + mode | speaker)
    + (1 | prompt)
    + (1 | h_start)
    + (1 | acc_phon)
    + (1 | fin_phon),
  data = m_corpus,
  control = lmerControl(
    optimizer = "optimx",
    calc.derivs = F,
    optCtrl = list(
      method = "nlminb",
      starttests = F,
      kkt = F
    )
  )
)

utt_mean_f0_full_mdl <- optimizeModel(utt_mean_f0_full_mdl)
write <- "output/utt_f0_full_phon"

utt_mean_f0_full.summary <- summariseLME(utt_mean_f0_full_mdl,
  run_step = F,
  write = paste0(write, "_anova.csv"),
  print_summary = F,
  plot_resids = F
)

predictions

utt_mean_f0.tidy <- analyseModel(
  utt_mean_f0_full_mdl,
  write = "output/utt_f0_full_phon",
  print_r2 = F
)

# utt_mean_f0.tidy$table %>% tidyNumbers(digits = 1) %>% tidyStatNumbers()
printTidyPredictions(utt_mean_f0_full_mdl,
  digits = 1
)

Utterance slope f0(t)

utt_slope_full_mdl <- lmer(
  utt_slope ~ mode
    + gender
    + (1 + mode | speaker)
    + (1 | prompt)
    + (1 | h_start)
    + (1 | acc_phon)
    + (1 | fin_phon),
  data = m_corpus,
  control = lmerControl(
    optimizer = "optimx",
    calc.derivs = F,
    optCtrl = list(
      method = "nlminb",
      starttests = F,
      kkt = F
    )
  )
)

utt_slope_full_mdl <- optimizeModel(utt_slope_full_mdl, verbose = F)

cat("\nTrimming model...")

utt_slope_mdl.trimmed <- update(
  utt_slope_full_mdl,
  data = m_corpus %>% filter(abs(scale(resid(utt_slope_full_mdl))) <= 3)
)

utt_slope_mdl.trimmed <- optimizeModel(utt_slope_mdl.trimmed, verbose = F)

predictions

utt_slope_full.tidy <- analyseModel(
  utt_slope_mdl.trimmed,
  write = "output/utt_slope_full_phon",
  plot_rounding = 2,
  print_r2 = F
)

# utt_slope_full.tidy$table %>% tidyNumbers(digits = 1) %>% tidyStatNumbers()
printTidyPredictions(utt_slope_mdl.trimmed,
  digits = 2
)
